Xinhua Review: Turning outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
Talent is the key to rural revitalization.
where to find talents?
Excellent returning migrant workers are an indispensable force.
Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26 th. Title: building outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiong, 34, lives in Guoyuan Village, Meishan City, Sichuan Province. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing with a monthly salary of 10,000 yuan and returned home to start a business.
After several years of hard work, he now has an annual income of more than one million yuan. He has become a well-known rich leader and has been selected into the "two committees" of the village.
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support agriculture and benefit agriculture, such as poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return home to start businesses, which has activated a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a province with a large population in western China and a large labor output province, has implemented the "excellent migrant workers back to the training project" according to the situation. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries have been generated from the outstanding migrant workers who have been returned to the village, 61,000 village reserve forces and more than 20,000 party members have been developed to provide a strong guarantee for winning the fight against poverty and implementing the strategy of rural revitalization.
Whether a well-off society is not a well-off society, the key lies in the villagers.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged workers in rural areas of China have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
However, objectively, it also leads to the "hollowing out" of rural areas to varying degrees, especially the weakening of rural grassroots organizations. The village party branch secretaries and party members show the characteristics of "one old and one low", that is, aging, low education, the village party organization leaders are not strong and the problem is prominent.
If rural talents and other factors have been flowing to cities in one direction, and the rural areas are in a state of "blood loss" and "anemia" for a long time, revitalization is empty talk.
To attract those migrant workers who are capable, conscious and willing to serve their hometown and guide them to return to their hometown to start businesses and become rich leaders, and select them into party members and rural cadres, and enrich the grassroots cadre team. This is the fundamental solution to the problem of rural party members and grassroots party organizations.
Excellent migrant workers need to stay and do a good job.
In recent years, Sichuan has paid close attention to the party building of migrant workers, and on the basis of strict selection criteria, it has established institutional mechanisms such as directional recruitment, service guarantee, training and promotion, selection and use of outstanding migrant workers, so that they can improve their ability, have security in their work, and there is hope in their life, so that they can really take root in the countryside.
This year is the final year of the decisive fight against poverty. Talent is the key factor to make a good connection between poverty alleviation and rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding migrant workers who have returned to their hometown and build them into a working team and a new force that can stay, fight and cannot be taken away, so as to provide strong organizational guarantee and talent support for rural poverty alleviation and development and revitalization.
