Seizing the Poetic "Yellow River Dream"
(Story of Poverty Reduction in China
China News Agency, Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) "Jiuqu Yellow River is thousands of miles of sand, and the waves and wind are from the end of the world."
The Yellow River, which aroused the lofty feelings of countless scholars, gave birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Now, Ningxia, which has the reputation of "blocking the south of the Yangtze River", is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream".
River beautiful "blue waves dream"
"The Yellow River in the world is rich in Ningxia". The Yellow River flows through Ningxia for 397 kilometers and is the "mother river" that nurtures one side.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, the development, utilization, management and protection of rivers and lakes are out of balance, and chaos such as excessive sewage discharge, reclamation of lakes and encroachment of water areas are emerged, resulting in black and smelly water, excessive water quality, dirty environment, and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the restoration of water ecology and striving to make the Yellow River beautiful and clear.
Water control should start from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government adopted the method of "raising standards+pollution control+strict management". All sewage in the industrial park was treated in a centralized manner. All the urban sewage treatment plants were discharged according to the first class A standard, the black and odorous water bodies in the urban built-up areas were basically eliminated, and the third batch of Chinese black and odorous water demonstration cities were successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake chief system in 2017, and now it has achieved full coverage of the five-level responsibility system of river and lake leaders in districts, cities, counties and villages.
64-year-old Gu Jincheng lives in a village near the Yellow River. He has witnessed the changes of the Yellow River: "The water used to have a bad smell, but after treatment, the smell is gone."
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is better and his life is more comfortable. Now he often goes for a walk along the Yellow River with his family to feel the clear water and blue sky.
"Wetland Dream"
Birds, green trees, plank roads and clear water... The beautiful scenery of Fan Zhongyan's "Sand Ou Xiangji" has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, forming many kinds of wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands and swamp wetlands along the way, which play an important role in promoting the rational utilization of water resources and water ecological balance, and also become an important international migration channel for birds.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have invested about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. At present, Yinchuan wetland covers an area of 19,200 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%. There are nearly 200 natural lakes and marshes, including 5 national wetland parks, 1 national urban wetland park, 6 autonomous regional wetland parks and 8 municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, especially in birds."Relict gull is an endangered bird. There are only more than 20,000 in the world, of which there are more than 2,000 in Yinchuan Wetland."
At the same time, Ningxia has set a red line of 500 meters for the wetland protection area on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law, stipulating that except for public welfare projects, no unit and individual is allowed to conduct development, construction and business activities within the protection area.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through pollution source treatment, comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology and terminal wetland construction, now the water quality of nine main drainage ditches in Ningxia has reached 100% of class IV standard, "now the water is clear, the fish are swimming, and the flowers are blooming."
"Drinking Water Dream"
Yinchuan City in Ningxia used to have a "embarrassing" title: the only city along the Yellow River "guarding the Yellow River and lacks water to drink".
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has begun to face the problem of water shortage in the peak of summer . The pain of water shortage in the past ten years has become a painful experience for many high-rise residents in the summer, but under the current situation that the major water sources are in the limit of overdraft and the urban underground has formed a large area of groundwater overdraft funnel area, water shortage has become a problem in Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking purified Yellow River water has become a good way to solve the drinking water problem of local residents.
Ding ming, deputy director of Yinchuan Municipal Water Affairs Bureau, said that in order to improve the living and production water demand of Yinchuan urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia timely started the water supply project of the western line of urban and rural areas in Yinchuan, replacing the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River water.
"On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially supplied water to the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County will also drink the Yellow River water."
Ding Ming said that Yinchuan Water Conservancy Department will consider the transformation of the integration of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply."In the next step, we will integrate all the scattered water supply points in rural areas into the western water supply project, and it is expected to basically realize the integration of urban and rural water supply in Yinchuan area by the end of this year."
