58 apps that infringe on user rights and interests have been exposed involving more than ten listed companies

The problems existing in these 58 apps include private collection of personal information, collection of personal information beyond the scope, frequent application for permission, excessive request for permission, difficulty in account cancellation, private sharing to a third party and denial of permission.
The Ministry of Industry and Information Technology requires that 58 apps should complete the rectification and implementation work before July 30. If they fail to make rectification within the time limit, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology will organize and carry out relevant disposal work in accordance with laws and regulations.
Zhongxin Jingwei reporter found that behind the 58 apps reported, more than 10 US stocks, Hong Kong stock and A-share listed companies were involved.
For example, "Fangduoduo" is a product of Fangduoduo, a US listed company. There are five major problems: collecting personal information privately, collecting personal information beyond the scope, sharing it to a third party privately, forcing users to use directional push function, and frequently applying for permission.
According to public information, Fangduoduo landed on NASDAQ in November 2019, and is "the first real estate intermediary company in China with SaaS (software service) mode of industrial Internet", providing online solutions for many intermediary merchants.
In response to the difficulty in cancellation of the "Qunar.com" APP account pointed out in the report, according to the Beijing News, Qunar.com responded that in order to prevent illegal products from making use of frequent registration and cancellation to seek profits, Qunar.com has set up an interval of one month on the basis of independent cancellation.
Considering the convenience of cancellation and the security of account, the cancellation has been changed to take effect immediately and is currently awaiting review.
A cyber security expert who did not want to be named told Zhongxin Jingwei client that the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology has issued three APP notifications of such violations of user rights and interests this year.
Among them, the three problems of private collection of personal information, excessive request for permission, and difficulty in account cancellation are repeatedly "management".
It can also be found from the notice that APP invasion of privacy has attracted more and more attention.
On July 24, when 58 apps infringing on user rights and interests were notified, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology said that it had issued a notice a few days ago to deploy and carry out a special rectification action to promote APP infringement on user rights and interests.
The special rectification will strengthen supervision and inspection in accordance with regulations, urge relevant enterprises to strengthen the protection of APP personal information, timely rectify and eliminate outstanding problems such as illegal collection, use of user personal information and harassment of users, deception and misleading of users, and ineffective implementation of management responsibility of application distribution platform, so as to purify APP application space.
Lewis family: John Lewis is a fighter "fighting for the weakest"
John Lewis, a US congressman and civil rights fighter, was remembered as a soldier "fighting for the weakest" at a memorial service held for him on Saturday (July 25).
Lewis's public memorial service has been held in Alabama since Saturday.
There were two memorial services on the first day.
At a public memorial service at the University of Troy in Alabama on Saturday, Lewis's five brothers and sisters and a nephew spoke of him as a loving, terrible, family oriented man.
Henry "Grant" Lewis, Lewis" his youngest brother, said at the meeting that "he devoted his life to helping others."
Samuel Lewis said that his mother had warned John "do not get into trouble, do not get into trouble."
He added that John did not listen to his mother warning. He said: "We all know that John always gets into trouble, always getting into trouble, but that is because he insisted on the right thing, that is a good trouble."
Lewis's brothers and sisters reminded people at the memorial service that John's most famous argument is to create "good trouble", that is, as long as it is for the sake of justice, it is not taboto stir up trouble.
John applied to Troy University in Troy, Alabama, where he was born, but Troy University, an all-white school at that time, rejected his application.
John Lewis, who preached the gospel to chickens on his farm as a child, eventually received a degree in religion and philosophy from Fisk University.
Years later, Troy University awarded Lewis an honorary doctorate.
Senator Doug Jones from Alabama said that the current protesters are "protesting peacefully and non-violently," just as Lewis did in the civil rights movement.
