Shenzhen solicits public opinions on the introduction of health regulations
Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (Reporter Mao SiQian and Bai Yu) encourage residents to do physical examination frequently and find problems as soon as possible; banned the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; establish an online game health examination system; Employers should be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel... Recently, the "health regulations of Shenzhen Special Economic Zone (Draft) were officially released, and Shenzhen residents will have their own "health law".
In order to encourage residents to take physical examination frequently and find problems as early as possible, the draft for opinions proposes that health departments should formulate a basic catalogue of health examination items according to different ages, occupations and other factors.
The cost of physical examination within the scope of the basic catalogue of health examination items shall be paid by the social medical insurance fund according to the standard of once per person per year.
According to the draft, it is clear that employers should rationally allocate human resources, arrange the work and rest time of employees, and implement a rotation system for employees with heavy mental and physical labor load to avoid excessive loss of human function or physical and mental health damage to employees' health, and strictly implement the paid vacation system for employees.
In addition, the employer should be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel, and regularly organize and carry out.
In terms of the physical and mental health of minors, the draft proposes that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors is prohibited, and the sales location of alcoholic beverages is restricted. Those who violate the regulations will be ordered to make corrections and fined 30,000 yuan.
In addition to "ban on drink", minors should also "exercise more".
According to the requirements of the draft, the school should arrange more than one hour of student sports activities every day.
For online games, public security, culture, radio, television, tourism and sports, network supervision, health and health departments should improve the health supervision system of Internet service business places, establish a health examination system of online games, and create a good communication space and culture for promoting the healthy growth of teenagers.
In addition, the draft also proposes that influenza patients must wear masks when entering and leaving public places, and medical and health institutions will be fined 20,000 yuan to reveal patients' privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the draft also requires that all departments in Shenzhen should assess the impact of the implementation of public policy on the health of the population before formulating planning and construction related to urban space planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and utilization, ecological environment protection, bio-medical industry development, regulatory documents and approving major construction projects and the implementation of major public service projects.
Those that have not been assessed or will have a serious adverse impact on urban public health or the health of residents shall not be formulated or approved for implementation.
