Valais police said that the witness called the police at 12:25 noon on the 25 th, saying he had witnessed a small plane falling from the sky.
A few minutes later, witness reported to the police again that smoke billowing from the crash site.
After receiving the report, the police quickly coordinated with fire police, medical staff and rescue workers and carried helicopters to the scene of the accident for rescue.
Rescue workers arrived at the crash site and found that all four people on board had been killed.
Police confirmed that the victims in the accident included two Swiss people aged 50 and 66, and two Austrians aged 46 and 50.
Police said that at present, the police are working with the Swiss Transportation Safety Investigation Committee to jointly investigate the cause of the crash.
