Xinjiang."sunflower fields" make good use of clean energy
2020-07-2615:43:42 Source: China News Net Author: Chen Haifeng Editor: Chen Haifeng
China News Agency, Hami, Xinjiang, July 26 th, Title: Xinjiang deeply cultivates "sunflower fields" and makes good use of clean energy
More than 6, 000 pentagonal heliostats of 48 square meters, each of 48 square meters, are arranged neatly in a circle, such as a silver "sunflower field". With the rotation of the sun, the sunlight is reflected to the heat absorption tower more than 200 meters high in the center, so as to realize power generation.
The reporter saw this scene on the 25 th.
"The so-called molten salt tower photothermal power generation is to reflect the sunlight through the mirror to the heat absorption tower to form heat energy, and then convert the heat energy into electric energy through traditional power generation technology."
Zhang Yong, deputy general manager of CLP Hami solar thermal power generation Co., Ltd., said that its design principle is similar to that of solar cookers used in rural areas in Northwest China, which should gather sunlight.
The power plant started construction in October 2017 and was connected to the grid at the end of last year. It covers an area of 6,600 mu and plans to install 14,500 heliostats.
"Compared with traditional solar power generation technology, its biggest advantage is that it can store the accumulated heat energy and generate electricity at night."
Zhang Yong said that the 13-hour heat storage system configured in the project can keep the generator set in continuous and stable operation without being affected by light changes; It can also quickly participate in power grid peak regulation according to the peak and valley demand of power grid load.
After the completion of the project, the project can generate 198 million kilowatt-hours of electricity per year, save more than 60,000 tons of standard coal each year, reduce emissions of more than 60 tons of sulfur dioxide, more than 60 tons of nitrogen oxides, about 20 tons of soot and more than 150,000 tons of carbon dioxide, and provide a steady stream of clean energy for the local area.
In addition, there is another silver "sunflower field" in Shichengzi photovoltaic industrial park in Hami City.
Hami Fuguang solar photovoltaic power station covers an area of more than 2,300 mu. The 714 power generation equipment that has been built also follow the sun rotation, always keeping the sunlight and the concentrating board at a 90 degrees right angle.
"We use dual-axis tracking concentrating power generation technology. Through unified integrated control, all power generation equipment will adjust the angle according to the height of the sun to maintain power generation efficiency."
Duan Mengqi, director of the power station, said that in good weather conditions, the power generation technology can improve the efficiency of traditional photovoltaic power generation by about 20%.
In the first half of this year, the power station has generated more than 7 million kilowatt-hours of electricity, supplementing local demand for electricity.
Shichengzi photovoltaic industrial park is currently a photovoltaic industrial demonstration park with the largest single scale and the most complete types of photovoltaic modules in Xinjiang, with a total of 38 photovoltaic power generation projects with a total installed capacity of 820,000 kilowatts.
In the first half of this year, the power generation exceeded 110 million kWh, an increase of 6% over the same period in 2019.
Hami is one of the regions with the best solar energy resources in China.
The annual average total solar radiation is more than 6200 megajoules per square meter, and the annual sunshine hours are about 3200 hours.
In recent years, the city has vigorously developed the photovoltaic industry and planted "sunflower fields".
A solar power generation scale with an installed capacity of more than 2.5 million kilowatts has been built. In the first half of this year, the photovoltaic power generation capacity of the city exceeded 1.4 billion kWh, an increase of about 14% year on year.
At present, there are more than 330 grid-connected photovoltaic power stations in Xinjiang with an installed capacity of over 10 million kilowatts.
It is estimated that photovoltaic power generation this year will reach 15 billion kWh, which can replace more than 6 million tons of standard coal.
Police report details of "female college students lost contact in Qinghai"
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, July 26 (Reporter Wang Jinjin and Zhou Zhe) Recently, "a female college student lost contact after traveling to Golmud, Qinghai" has aroused the attention of netizens.
The Public Security Bureau of Golmud City, Haixi Mongolian and Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture, Qinghai Province, reported on the 26th that Huang Moumou a student of a university in Nanjing is still in a state of lost contact and police in many places are going deep along the route of Huang Moumou and actively carrying out the search work.
On July 10, 2020, the public security branch of Golmud Public Security Bureau in Haixi Prefecture received a notice from the higher level that Huang Moumou, a student of a university in Nanjing, took the Z164 train from Nanjing to Golmud on July 5, and on July 9, he turned off his mobile phone and lost contact at the southwest area of Qingshui River of Sonandajie protection station in Qumalai County, Yushu Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture, Qinghai Province, asking for assistance.
According to the investigation by Golmud Public Security Bureau, Huang entered Qinghai Province at 19:54 on July 6 and arrived in Golmud at 4:00 on July 7.
At 8:00 on the same day at 8:00 on the Yellow River Hotel in Golmud City and arrived at the Sonandajie protection station in Hoh Xil at 12:00. The taxi driver returned alone, Huang arrived in the Qingshui River area near the Sonandajie protection station at 15:00 on the 7th and turned off in the area at about 18:00 on the 9 th.
During further investigation, the police found that Huang had passed through the Najigou checkpoint at 17:07 on July 13.
Naijigou checkpoint is a checkpoint set up by Naqu city of the Tibet Autonomous Region in Nanshankou, Golmud City. Because there is no video monitoring at the checkpoint, it is impossible to determine the information of the person and the vehicle. The police can only drive along the way to find and coordinate the checkpoints along the way to contact the Public Security Bureau of Golmud City.
According to the latest situation, at 1:00 a.m. on July 26, the Golmud City Public Security Bureau organized rescue forces to carry rescue equipment to the unfreezing spring protection station and Sonandajie protection station along the Qinghai-Tibet highway to look for it, and actively contacted the Sichuan police, Tibet police and Nanjing police to work together. At present, the search and rescue work is still continuing.
The local police hope to the majority of netizens and all sectors of society if they have relevant clues, timely to the Golmud police and Nanjing Jiangning police in order to find the missing person Huang Moumou as soon as possible.
At the same time, relevant experts suggest that tourists should be standardized, rational and civilized in outdoor activities, pay attention to roadside warning signs at any time, do not venture into no man's land, and report to the police in time in case of emergencies.
