Brazilian researchers divided 667 patients from 55 hospitals across the country into three groups and conducted clinical trials; This is to compare the therapeutic effects of hydroxychloroquine alone or in combination with other enzyme azithromycin to analyze whether it will help improve the condition of mild and moderate patients with COVID-19.
The results showed that hydroxychloroquine not only had no therapeutic effect, but might have harmful side effects on organs.
This study was carried out by several authoritative hospitals in Brazil, such as Hospital Israel Albert Einstein, heart hospital (HCor) and Hospital Sírio-Libanês) in collaboration with the Brazilian Institute of clinical Research (BCRI) and the Brazilian intensive care research network (BRICNet).
