With the decline of Yu'e Bao's income, the "post-90 s" not only did not escape from Yu'e Bao, but began to "retaliate" to save money?
According to the "post-90 s saving report" (2020 version) released by the China New Economic Research Institute and Alipay recently, in the first half of the year, the "post-90 s" were more likely to save money: the average amount of money saved increased by nearly 40% compared with 2019.
Interestingly, the "post-90 s" tend to start saving from a small sum of money, with 60% of them saving less than 20 yuan on average ...
Saving money with Yu'ebao has also become a saving habit of the post-90 s.
Data show that among the 700 million Yuebao users, 134 million are "post-90 s".
There are 17.4 million "post-90 s" in China, that is to say, about three out of every four "post-90 s" in the country are saving money with Yuebao
At present, the 7-day annualized rate of return of Yu'ebao and other monetary funds has fallen to about 1.5% from a level higher than 2% at the beginning of the year.
Even so, it did not affect the pace of "post-90 s" saving money.
In the context of the "saving effect" of Yu'e Bao, many young people who are used to using Yu'ebao are directly transformed into "basic people".
According to Alipay data, as of July 13, the number of new "basic people" on Alipay has more than doubled year-on-year in the past month, and more and more young people have achieved "advanced" financial management on Alipay.
Some analysts believe that the inflow of funds from Yu'ebao into the stock market is also an important reason for the clear decline in the share of money funds in June.
The report also shows that "post-90 s" girls are more likely to save more money, 20% more than boys on average compared with men. Among the users who hold funds on Alipay platform, 60% are men, and women tend to choose more stable financial management methods compared with men.
After saving money, what are the plans for the post-90 s?
According to Alipay data, the "post-90 s" have the habit of saving money for their goals, and the number of users who take travel as a saving goal.
Affected by the epidemic, many "post-90 s" save money to prepare for travel after the epidemic; The reopening of movie theaters also provides a new way to shift from saving money to consumption.
