France increases military investment in space
French Defense Minister Florence Pali said on the 24th that France will add hundreds of millions of euros in space defense budget to develop space military forces to prevent "unfriendly actions" that other countries may make in outer space.
Pali told Provence that day that from 2019 to 2025, the budget for French space military projects will increase to 4.3 billion euros (5 billion US dollars) from the previously proposed 3.6 billion euros (about 4.2 billion US dollars) to 4.3 billion euros (5 billion US dollars).
According to the French Military Planning Act from 2019 to 2025 approved by the French Parliament in 2018, France is expected to update the existing observation satellites and communication satellites, launch three electromagnetic listening satellites, and improve the modernization level of space surveillance radar.
French President Emmanuel Macron announced in July last year that a space military command and an "aviation and space force" will be set up within the French Air Force.
Pali said she will officially announce the formation of the space force when she visits a military academy in Saron, Provence later.
Pali said that the space force is part of the air force and will have 500 personnel by 2025.
"The idea of space serving the common interests of science in the past is gone forever. Now space is a place where countries compete for global hegemony."
Pali reiterated Macron's previous statement, saying that France has no intention of provoking an arms race.
"We are by no means engaged in an arms race. But I have a responsibility to thoroughly recognize the threats we may face."
Pali recalled the surveillance of a military satellite shared by France and Italy in 2017.
She said it was a Russian satellite.
The Russian side denies this statement.
Pali said that France "soon" will have a small patrol satellite capable of detect and lock "the black hands behind those unfriendly actions".
According to French media, the reason why France seeks to set up a space force is that US President Donald Trump asked the US Department of Defense in February last year to draft a bill to establish a space force.
Trump signed the National Defense Authorization Act in December last year, approving the establishment of the space force.
Some experts worry that these US measures have accelerated the militarization of US space and may trigger a new round of space arms race.
