(Reporter Yang Zhaokui) The "China shared accommodation development report 2020" (hereinafter referred to as the "Report") released by the sharing economy Research Center of the State Information Center recently shows that due to the impact of the epidemic, in the first five months of 2020, the transaction volume of China's shared accommodation market decreased by 72.1% year on year.
However, the shared accommodation market began to pick up in March, and the market transaction volume, order volume and number of visitors gradually recovered.
