The longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area
2020-07-2617:34:48 Source: China News Net Author: Chen Haifeng Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the small Three Gorges tunnel.
Photo provided by China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Company
Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd. on the 26th that the small Three Gorges tunnel of Zhengwan high-speed railway with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers was completed on the same day.
It is understood that the small Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir area, but also the longest single-hole double line high-speed railway tunnel with a design speed of 350 km/h among the projects currently under construction in China.
Zheng-Wan high-speed railway is located in Henan, Hubei and Chongqing provinces and cities. It connects Beijing-Guangzhou and Xulan high-speed railway in the north of Zhengzhou and Yu-Wan high-speed railway in the south of Wanzhou, which is an important part of the riverside passage
The small Three Gorges Tunnel of Zhengwan high-speed railway was completed on the 26 th.
The picture shows the scene.
The Zhengwan high-speed railway starts from Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and runs southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City and Xiangyang City of Hubei Province to Wanzhou District of Chongqing City. The new line has a total length of about 818 kilometers, a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou-Xiangyang section has been put into operation in advance on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up its construction.
The Small Three Gorges Tunnel, which is completed on the 26 th, is a control project of the Zhengwan high-speed railway. The project is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers and a maximum buried depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017, and the tunnel was completed on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Guojun, head of Zhengwan high-speed railway tunnel design of China Railway Eryuan Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the small Three Gorges Tunnel is located in a very complex terrain and geological condition, facing risks such as karst, mud inrush and large deformation of soft rock, which is a class I high-risk tunnel, which is extremely difficult for tunnel design and construction.
"During the construction of the project, we used geological survey method, geophysical exploration method and advanced drilling method to advance geological prediction, and adopted special design plans for more than 30 karst caves of various types. For example, a bridge with a length of 24 meters is designed and built to cross a large karst cave with a longitudinal length of over 10 meters and a depth of over 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid tunnel settlement." Wang Guojun said.
According to the introduction of the China Railway Tunnel Bureau of the construction party, the construction of the tunnel adopted the combination of dredging and blocking through the construction of horizontal tunnel, grouting and blocking the water, strengthening the tunnel structure support and building the sewage treatment station, which not only ensure the orderly progress of the project, but also avoid the damage of construction drainage to the water body of the small Three Gorges scenic spots. At the same time, it successfully overcomes the construction problems such as the seven kilometers of soft rock large deformation and so on, and the daily maximum water inflow of 157,000 cubic meters.
After the completion and opening of Zhengwan high-speed railway will become a new convenient and fast passenger transport main channel from Southwest China to Central Plains, North China and Northeast China. It is of great significance to improve the capacity and quality of northeast railway channel in Southwest China, improve the regional road network layout, speed up the development and urbanization along the route, promote regional coordinated development and promote the implementation of the western development strategy. It is of great significance.
