Greenland opens a new round of mixed reform
On July 26, Rao Xianjun, a reporter from the Economic Observer network, Greenland Holdings (600606. SH) issued a "suggestive announcement on the state-owned shareholders plan to transfer part of the company's shares and resume trading through public solicitation of the transfere".
According to the content of the announcement, in order to further deepen the reform of state-owned assets and state-owned enterprises, optimize the structural adjustment of state-owned assets, and improve the ownership structure of Greenland, Shanghai real estate (Group) Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as "Shanghai real estate") and Shanghai urban investment (Group) Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as "Shanghai city") plan to transfer part of the shares held by the company through public solicitation of the transferee. The total proportion of shares to be transferred shall not exceed 17.5% of the total share capital of Greenland.
The price of the shares to be transferred this time shall not be lower than that of the higher of the following two: the arithmetic average of the daily weighted average price of the 30 trading days before the suggestive announcement date (July 27, 2020); The audited net asset value per share of the company in the latest fiscal year.
At present, there is still no conclusion on the new strategic investors of Greenland. According to the information announced in the announcement, the new strategic investors need to pay about 14 billion yuan for the 17.5% equity transferred in the mixed reform of Greenland.
It is worth noting that after the completion of the share transfer, Greenland is expected to still have no controlling shareholders and actual controllers, but the control structure may change greatly.
Since its establishment, Greenland Holdings has carried out many institutional reforms: from 1992 to 1997, it operated under the pure state-owned system; From 1997 to 2013, it established and continuously improved the shareholding system of state-owned holding and employee shareholding system; From 2013 to 2015, strategic investors were introduced to form a mixed ownership system with cross-shareholding and mutual integration of state-owned and non-public capital. Since 2015, it has been listed as a whole and become a public company.
Greenland's current mixed reform plan is similar to Greey. In December 2019, Zhuhai Mingjun, led by Gaoyi capital, took over 15% equity of Gree Electric (000651. SZ) with 41.662 billion yuan. Gree Group retired as a minority shareholder. After the completion of the mixed reform, Gree Electric has implemented modern enterprise management methods such as the executive incentive plan and no actual control structure .
Shanghai real real estate and Shanghai urban investment are state-owned enterprise groups wholly owned by the Shanghai state-owned assets and enterprises of the Shanghai SASAC. Zhang Yuliang, chairman and president of Greenland Holdings, said that Greenland is an important measure for Shanghai to promote the comprehensive reform of state-owned assets and state-owned enterprises in accordance with the requirements of the Party Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and accelerate the comprehensive reform of state-owned assets and state-owned enterprises in the new stage of the reform of state-owned assets and state-owned enterprises in accordance with the requirements of the Communist Party of China, which fully shows the new thinking of reform in accordance with local conditions and according to the introduction of new excellent strategic shareholders to listed companies, support enterprises to further improve the degree of marketization, enhance the degree of freedom of operation and management, and accelerate the full release of reform vitality.
