Membrane separation technology helps crack the "greenhouse effect"
Schematic diagram of preparation technology of new mixed matrix membrane
Our reporter Shang Rui reports: A few days ago, the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team of Tianjin University has made great progress in "carbon dioxide capture by membrane separation" and successfully developed a new mixed matrix membrane preparation technology, greatly improving the carbon dioxide capture performance of membrane materials.
Correlation results have been published as the cover article of the international journal Greenhouse gas: Science and technology.
The "greenhouse effect" is a major environmental problem that haunts human development, and carbon dioxide emission is the culprit of the "greenhouse effect".
How to efficiently capture and use carbon dioxide emitted by human beings is the focus of scientists.
"Membrane separation" is a new carbon dioxide capture technology, which separates carbon dioxide gas with the help of membrane materials, and has the characteristics of high efficiency, energy saving and simple operation.
How to make the membrane material "take a deep breath" and improve the efficiency of gas separation is the bottleneck difficulty of carbon dioxide capture by membrane separation method.
The scientific research team of Tianjin University innovated ideas and explored the influence of different solvents on membrane gas separation performance through repeated experiments.
The experimental results show that using N-methylpyrrolidone as the preparation solvent, the distribution of carbon nanotubes in the membrane material is more uniform and "more permeable", which effectively improves the gas separation efficiency and rate of the membrane material.
The carbon dioxide separation performance of the mixed matrix membrane prepared by this new technology is close to the theoretical separation upper limit of this kind of membrane material.
"The new technology provides a new idea to capture carbon dioxide by membrane separation."
Li Run, a member of the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team of Tianjin University, said: "We hope that this technology can provide strong support for future coal-fired power plants and chemical enterprises to deal with flue gas and play a major role in controlling greenhouse gas emissions and other fields."
Before volunteering to fill in the report
2020-07-2702:22:36 Source: Chongqing Morning Post Author: Yu Xiao Editor: Yu Xiao
understand what is professional grade difference before volunteering to fill in
Every year, when filling in the college entrance examination, there are students or parents who do not understand the terms involved in the voluntary reporting, which affects the voluntary application.
This year, Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University and Beijing University of Chemical Technology jointly issued the enrollment policy in 2020 to cancel the professional grade difference.
What is the meaning of professional grade difference and what is its significance in voluntary reporting?
There are three ways of professional distribution rules
Experts remind that before filling in the application for volunteer, you must read the "enrollment regulations" of your favorite school and understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the proportion of file transfer and the rules of major allocation and so on.
Professional distribution rules refer to the three main ways of professional admission: professional priority, score priority and professional grade difference.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be specified in the enrollment regulations.
However, the admission principle of some colleges and universities is to give priority to the total score, and there is no difference between majors.
That is to say, the candidates in the admission range will be queued according to the total score. When the score does not reach the first professional volunteer admission score line, it will see whether they have reached the second professional volunteer admission score line, and so on until the admission to the last professional volunteer. There is no grade difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called "professional grade difference" means that when colleges and universities arrange candidates for their majors, they determine the admission majors of volunteer candidates of different majors according to one or several scores published in the enrollment regulations. This score value is "professional grade difference".
That is to say, the difference between the scores of the first professional volunteer and the non-first professional volunteer of the colleges and universities, and the grade difference scores between the professional volunteers, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point and so on.
For example.
Suppose the student Xiao Ming applied for college A and scored 560 points. His professional volunteers are: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering and e-commerce. The professional admission of university A adopts the method of professional grade difference, which is divided into 2 points, 1 point, 1 point and 0 point.
If Xiaoming's first major meets the professional admission requirements and the major has a planned balance, Xiaoming will be admitted to the "computer" major; If the computer is not admitted, his score will be subtracted by 2 points. According to the score of 558 points and the first major volunteers to apply for "international trade" candidates to determine whether they meet the professional admission conditions; If it is still not satisfied, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (namely 557 points) for the third professional volunteer "automatic" admission; If it is still not satisfied, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (556 points) for the admission of the fourth major. If the subsequent major still cannot meet its professional wishes, the score will not be reduced, and so on.
Different universities have different professional grades
With the popularity of parallel volunteer, many colleges and universities have cancelled the professional level difference, but some colleges and universities still retain this method this year. According to the "enrollment regulations" published by various colleges and universities, more than 20 universities have set up professional grade difference this year.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Dianli University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight Academy, etc.
In these universities, each university has a different professional level.
Some colleges and universities have a grade difference in each major, such as Ningxia University. The candidates who have been submitted to the university will be admitted according to the order in which the candidates fill in the professional volunteers.
However, some universities have set different professional grades between different majors.
For example, in Jimei University, the total score of professional volunteer grade difference is 4 points, that is, the grade difference between the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteers is 3 points, and there is no grade difference between other professional volunteers, which is regarded as parallel volunteer, and the professional grade difference between other professional volunteers and adjusted professional volunteers is 1 point.
When filling in their volunteers, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the school reported to see if there is a professional grade difference and what is the form of the grade difference. While fully considering the scores, they should also reasonably analyze the school and major to be selected. If the colleges and universities adopts the grade difference method for admission in the enrollment regulations, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the majors when choosing the major, so as to improve the admission rate.
