Hong Kong, July 25 (Xinhua News Agency, Hong Kong Special Administrative Region Government Secretary for Commerce and Economic Development Qiu Tenghua said on the 25th that all APEC member economies should act in concert to fight the epidemic and promote economic recovery, and should avoid the establishment of unnecessary trade barriers in accordance with the rights and obligations set up by the World Trade Organization.
Qiu Tenghua made the above remarks while participating in the video conference of trade ministers on the fight against COVID-19 pneumonia held by the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) on the 25 th.
At this meeting, the participating ministers exchanged views on the substantive plans that APEC can take to respond to the impact of COVID-19 and promote economic recovery in the region.
Qiu Tenghua said that the public health and economic crisis triggered by the epidemic has had an unprecedented and profound impact on society and economy.
"We are in a double battle. We must overcome the epidemic before we can recover the economy.
We have to have a clear goal. The virus is our common enemy. Only through cooperation can win, otherwise it will only fail."
Qiu Tenghua said that the series of trade restrictions triggered by the COVID-19 epidemic will not help control the epidemic.
Trade is the key solution to the current problem and should not be regarded as the problem.
He condemned all discriminatory and divided policies and measures, and urged all economies to keep their borders open at this critical moment, maintain the smooth operation of the supply chain, and avoid establishing trade barriers or adopting irrational trade policies.
