Chengdu people gather to watch the US consulate, police prevent people from "looking too happy"
In response to the US closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston, China announced the closure of the US Consulate General in Chengdu on Friday.
On Saturday, the badge of the U.S. consulate was removed, and on Sunday, a dark glass car left the consulate amid boos from passers-by.
On Sunday, many Chengdu people gathered in front of the US consulate to take pictures. Those who had not been here also came to have a look driven by curiosity about current events.
Agence News Agency reporter from Chengdu Station also visited the US Consulate in Chengdu and reported that there were an endless stream of curious people, and many parents took their children for a walk to watch the consulate, take photos of the buildings or take selfies.
The consulate is surrounded by guards, and the police "correct" people's behavior from time to time. They do not seem to allow any unusual behavior: a woman was stopped as soon as she was preparing to sing a red song, and a guard confiscated a banner.
But residents of a nearby residential building managed to pull up a giant Chinese flag on their balcony and slogans of support for China.
The U.S. Consulate in Chengdu opened in 1985, covering all U.S. consular affairs in Southwest China, especially the Tibet Autonomous Region.
According to a reporter from Israel News Agency Chengdu station, the Chinese government's response to the United States is relatively restrained: many Chinese people asked the government to close the US consulate in Hong Kong online, but the official only said that "closing the US consulate in Chengdu is a necessary and legal response to the unreasonable behavior of the United States".
In addition to Chengdu, the United States also has consulates in Guangdong, Shanghai, Shenyang, Wuhan and Hong Kong in China.
Start of the large-scale financial media action "live in the village to see poverty alleviation"-Today's news-Hunan Daily-Huasheng Online
Hunan Daily · New Hunan client July 25 (Reporter) On July 25, the large-scale financial media action "live from the village to see poverty alleviation" sponsored by the financial program center of China Central Radio and TV Station started from Xuzhou, Jiangsu Province, and two caravans carrying 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system slowly drove out of the scene under the watch of the guests at the scene.
General Secretary Xi Jinping pointed out that "2020 is a milestone year. We will build a well-off society in an all-round way and achieve the goal of the first century.2020 is also the year of decisive victory in poverty alleviation."
The large-scale financial media action "go to the village live to watch poverty alleviation" is an important measure taken by the financial program center of China Central Radio and Television to coordinate with this major theme and do a good job in poverty alleviation propaganda.
The action will go into poverty alleviation villages in more than 20 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the central government, dig out the stories of poverty alleviation, directly attack the great changes in the appearance of the villages, and show how the villagers break through the plight of survival and development and move towards the road of prosperity.
The operation will last more than three months.
The reporter started from Xuzhou, divided into two routes, all the way to the southwest line, passing through Anhui, Hubei, Jiangxi, Hunan, Guangxi, Guizhou, Sichuan, Chongqing, Yunnan, Tibet and other places; The other way takes the northwest route, passing through Henan, Shaanxi, Gansu, Qinghai, Xinjiang, Ningxia, Inner Mongolia, Shanxi, Hebei and other places, with a journey of more than 10,000 kilometers.
In the form of reporting, "go to the village live to see poverty alleviation" boldly integrated.
The economic development of the villages visited by the caravan will be broadcast through the CCTV financial channel of the Central Radio and TV station, the sound of the CCTV economy and the new media of China.
Among them, the TV live broadcast will be mainly completed in the midday news program World Finance of CCTV financial channel (first broadcast time:12:00-13:00 from Monday to Sunday), and the golden news column "Economic Information Network" of CCTV financial channel will set up a report column on poverty alleviation (first broadcast time:20:30-21:30 from Monday to Sunday).
At the same time, the caravan will carry out a 1-hour live broadcast of each village on the CCTV financial client for each hour. The audience can watch the live broadcast and participate in the lucky draw by downloading the CCTV financial APP.
In terms of technology application and studio design, "going to the village live to see poverty alleviation" has the courage to make a breakthrough and pioneered the "outfield new media caravan".
The car is equipped with 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system, and uses 5G+4K/8K+AI technology to realize the organic combination of online and offline, large screen and small screen, and TV broadcasting.
It is equipped with three news studio area, and the studio area is converted into a container, with a length of 12 meters, a width of 2.55 meters and a height of 3.98 meters. The box adopts a hydraulic automatic expansion structure, which can turn up to 120 degrees.
The studio area can also be expanded automatically. and the external expansion platform, covering an area of more than 50 square meters, which can meet the scene requirements of most programs.
At present, Dongchuan District of Kunming City is already hot in summer, and what is hotter than the weather is the poverty alleviation workshop next to the resettlement site.
"Now, as soon as you leave home, you go into the factory to make money and care for your family. Thanks to the free vocational skills training organized by the trade union."
Walking into the poverty alleviation workshop of electronic components processing and poverty alleviation workshop in Tongdu Street, Dongchuan District, a busy picture comes into view.
Lu Ling, in her 40 s, is a single mother who takes care of her children and elderly parents.
When she was in the most difficult time, the Dongchuan District Federation of trade unions helped to come up with ideas and find ways to "send charcoal in the snow" after running.
Since 2018, Lu Ling has enjoyed assistance policies such as housing, schooling, social security and employment, as well as assistance funds issued by trade unions at all levels.
This year, her child has successfully graduated and got a job. She herself has got a job and income after participating in skills training, and got out of trouble at the end of April.
It is reported that the Dongchuan District General organized special skills training project to help poverty alleviation is part of the skills training work of Yunnan Federation of Trade unions.
According to the characteristics of the workers who are in difficulties in the relocation and resettlement sites for poverty alleviation and resettlement sites in the district, the district will conduct an in-depth investigation to understand the training needs and determine the types of training work. In the near future, it plans to train a total of 450 electricians, welders, and bakers.
Recently, Li Yi, an employee of the Yunnan Menglian County Sub-branch of Agricultural Bank of China, wrote a sincere letter of gratitude to the County Federation of Trade unions.
In the letter, she expressed her sincere gratitude to the trade union for the golden autumn grant from August 2013 to January 2017 to help her complete her studies.
In 2004, Li Yi's father died in a car accident, and her mother was included in the file of employees in difficulty. Since then, she has always enjoyed the care of the file establishment policy
With the help of the local trade union, Li Yi successfully completed her studies.
Since 2016, 3809 households have been lifted out of poverty through institutional guarantee and precise assistance.
The success of Lv Ling's family and Li Yi is a microscope of the work of Yunnan trade union to promote the work of difficult workers to get out of difficulties.
According to Duan Kaiyuan, a staff member of the Legal and Rights Protection Department of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions, the provincial general manager strengthened the dynamic management of the files of employees in difficulties, promoted the normalization of filing work, and timely included the difficult employees who meet the requirements for filing into the assistance system; We will broaden the application channels for employees in difficulties, and use WeChat to open an online filing service platform for employees in difficulty, so as to facilitate the employees in difficulties to take the initiative to report in time.
During the epidemic period, it was difficult to go out to work. In order to help the workers with difficulties in file to relieve the pressure of life, Yunnan Province arranged a total of more than 13 million yuan to send warm funds, according to the standard of 2,000 yuan per household for the difficult workers at the national level and 1,500 yuan per household for the difficult workers at the provincial level.
At the same time, the provincial head office connects with various Internet recruitment platforms such as human resources and social security departments and Zhaopin Recruitment to push recruitment information to employees in difficulties, and provide employment consultation, employment guidance and other services.
